Before starting pahse 4 how we are going to ensure uniqueness of shorturl13:50Great question! Here's how SmashLink will ensure uniqueness:

Strategy — Base62 Encoding + DB Constraint (Double Safety)
Layer 1 — Base62 Encoding
Convert the database auto-incremented id of the URL record into a Base62 string (characters: a-z, A-Z, 0-9).
ID: 1       → shortCode: "0000001"
ID: 99999   → shortCode: "0004QjV"
ID: 1000000 → shortCode: "000AMgY"
Since every DB id is unique by nature, every generated short code is guaranteed unique — no collision possible.

Layer 2 — DB Unique Constraint (Safety Net)
java@Column(unique = true, nullable = false)
private String shortCode;
```
Even if something unexpected happens, the database **rejects duplicates** at the constraint level.

