## The Flow
```
User sends long URL
       ↓
Save Url entity (id auto-generated by DB)
       ↓
Encode id → Base62 shortCode
       ↓
Update entity with shortCode
       ↓
Return: smashlink.io/abc123

Why Base62 over other approaches?
Approach    CollisionRisk   Predictable Simple
RandomUUID     Possible         ❌       ❌
MD5/SHA hash   Possible         ❌       ❌
Base62 on ID    Zero            ✅       ✅
Snowflake ID    Zero            ✅       ❌
Base62 on auto-increment ID wins — zero collision, short output, simple logic.

Short Code Length
With Base62 and 7 characters you get 62⁷ = 3.5 trillion unique URLs. More than enough. ✅